  "text": "The most numerous cells in the CNS are the macroglia, which include the astrocytes and oligodendrocytes. Macroglia perform many functions but are key for the homeostatic functioning of the CNS through the provision of structural and nutritional support for neurons and endothelial cells [CITATION_1] .",
